Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated).

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of baking paper or
cling film.

Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a
#saucepan{} until it's 2-3cm thick.

Season with salt and the @peri peri seasoning{}, then press the seasoning into
the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Season with salt and pepper.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} into another #bowl{}. Season with salt and
pepper and mix well.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely
coated. Transfer to clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely coat
the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3
> mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high
and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes} total. Turn
every 2-3 mins and adjust the heat if necessary.

Once cooked, transfer to a clean plate lined with #kitchen paper{}. Season with
salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Garlic Peas ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #small frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat.
Season with salt and pepper.

== Cheesy Chips ==

When the chips have a few mins left, scatter them with the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and return to the oven until melted,
~{2-3%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Serve the crispy chicken on plates with the cheesy chips and peas alongside.

Add a dollop of @tomato ketchup{2%dollops} for dipping. Enjoy!